    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">In this deck, you should bid 2 burdens. If you get the chance, go first and play The Gaffer with Bag End. Merry&#39;s there for back-up while people like Boromir, Gandalf, and Aragorn stop the minions. Thrarin throws himself in in a hopeless situation, while Filibert stops Bally&#39;s second time around. This could be considered a fun deck due to it&#39;s lacking of necessary rares. Please focus on the positive or whatever needs to be improved. Although we all think it, please don&#39;t say that this deck is a piece of crap. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
